&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;PubMatic is a recognized leader in audience solutions, having built one of the industry’s most advanced and comprehensive audience data platforms&amp;nbsp;on the supply side. Our suite of audience capabilities has been a cornerstone of how the open programmatic ecosystem navigates the shift toward privacy-first, durable&amp;nbsp;advertising,&amp;nbsp;enabling advertisers to achieve relevance and strong ROAS without reliance on deprecated identifiers like the third-party cookie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;As signal loss accelerates and contextual and first-party data become the foundation of modern audience strategies, PubMatic’s Audience Solutions portfolio is at the center of this transformation. Our flagship capability, Connect, is a leading data marketplace that enables data vendors to monetize and manage their audiences against programmatic&amp;nbsp;deals,&amp;nbsp;driving incremental revenue to our publishers and better outcomes for advertisers. Today,&amp;nbsp;Connect&amp;nbsp;powers partnerships with dozens of premium contextual, behavioral, and intent data providers, and continues to scale rapidly as the market moves toward&amp;nbsp;cookieless&amp;nbsp;buying.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;More recently, PubMatic has taken a leadership role in&amp;nbsp;agentic&amp;nbsp;advertising revolution.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;PubMatic launched and executed the industry’s first fully autonomous campaign in December 2025.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Audience Solutions&amp;nbsp;is playing&amp;nbsp;a critical role in shaping that future, working jointly with data providers, curators, and buyers to build this new ecosystem.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Associate Vice President, Audience Solutions, will own and grow PubMatic’s global Connect business, lead our curation efforts, and lead the audience aspects of our broader agentic vision. This is a high-impact general management role that spans go-to-market strategy, sales, customer success, product input, product marketing, pricing, and team development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The AVP will&amp;nbsp;be responsible for&amp;nbsp;defining the Audience Solutions business strategy,&amp;nbsp;acquiring&amp;nbsp;new Connect data partners, and scaling existing partner relationships. As the industry continues to evolve,&amp;nbsp;with AI-driven audience modeling, clean room integrations, and privacy-preserving data collaboration becoming table stakes,&amp;nbsp;this leader will position PubMatic at the forefront of next-generation audience infrastructure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;•&quot; data-font=&quot;&quot; data-listid=&quot;2&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;•&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Define and execute th

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role as a Business Intelligence Associate is to work with the product and machine learning team to automate the process of manual forecasting and identify the root causes. You are expected to detect anomalies/issues early, identify root causes, track revenue and spend trends on an hourly/daily/weekly/monthly basis against the forecast. Coordination with multiple teams to fix problems with rollouts/ releases and ensure leadership always has an accurate view of performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the health of the business via tools such as our anomaly detection software and other dashboards, and keep cross-functional stakeholders aligned on the health of key input metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hourly and daily (Real-time monitoring): Monitor the hourly trend continuously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Revenue declines must be assessed to find the root cause and verify if the decline is associated with any product release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allocate the identified cause to the corresponding teams and assess the next actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inform the Network Operations Center team to trigger P1/P2 alerts based on the severity of the revenue decline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly (Medium Term Monitoring): Own the revenue forecasting process and provide executive updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define variance thresholds that trigger deeper analysis to understand reasons behind movements of key dimensions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate any metrics that show signs of decay or are deviating from the norm and find the root cause.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly (Long Term Monitoring): Lead the monthly review process with Marketplace, Product, and Engineering stakeholders to track the key drivers of our spend on an ongoing basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be intimately involved in the quarterly and annual planning process and be aware of what assumptions went into the plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the project manager of investigations. Cross-functionally manage workstreams with account stakeholders to complete analyses and troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive Communication: Share insights and learnings on long-term and short-term trends with a broader set of stakeholders to inform strategic planning and GTM execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide regular updates on Steering Committees. Revenue Monitoring Process Improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce “blind spots” by developing new monitoring frameworks and incorporating new data sources into existing monitoring processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product Management and external vendors to improve existing anomaly detection solutions, based on KPI performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rollout and Recovery Tracking: Work closely with the monetization product team to track and quantify the impact of product releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;d Love for You to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven 3 to 5 years of experience in data analysis, or a similar role, is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical skills such as Excel, Looker, MYSQL, forecasting, impact measurement, AB Testing, are a must.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Excel macro/VBA, Python, and Ad Tech experience is good to have.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with GenAI-based tools like Cursor and Claude will be an added advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of data manipulation and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with anomaly detection techniques, including supervised and unsupervised learning methods, time-series analysis, and outlier detection algorithms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding big data technologies and tools like Hadoop, Spark, or cloud platforms (AWS, Google Cloud, etc.) is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
